---
import Poem from '../../layouts/Poem.astro';
---
<Poem title="Low Point" description="Two companion poems about childhood poverty, the child tax credit, and the hidden costs of growing up with scarcity.">
  <section>
    <div class="container">
      <div class="low-point-chart-wrap">
        <p class="low-point-epigraph">
          <em>The rate of US childhood poverty reached its lowest point in 2021 due to the pandemic child tax
          credit emergency relief program.<sup>1,2</sup></em>
        </p>
        <div id="low-point-chart"></div>
        <div class="low-point-coda">
          <span class="coda-line">But let's not get emotional,</span>
          <span class="coda-line coda-line--tilted">let's look at facts.</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="sr-only">
        <p>LOW POINT. The SPM child poverty rate more than halved, from 12 to 5.2 percent, from 2018 to 2021. The rate of US childhood poverty reached its lowest point in 2021 due to the pandemic child tax credit emergency relief program.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="poem-about">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>About This Poem</h2>
      <p>'Low Point' charts how US childhood poverty reached its lowest point in 2021 when the pandemic child tax credit sent up to $300/kid/month to families in need — then Congress let it expire. The annotated graph turns dry policy data into a visual narrative about what happens when a proven intervention is abandoned.</p>
      <p class="mt-sm" style="font-size:0.9rem; color:var(--color-text-secondary);">This interactive version animates the data to unfold the story sequentially. Hover over any data point to see the exact poverty rate.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="explore">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Explore the Data</h2>

      <div class="explore-card">
        <h5>Supplemental Poverty Measure: Child Poverty Rate, 2009–2022</h5>
        <p class="explore-source">Source: <a href="https://www.census.gov/newsroom/stories/poverty-awareness-month.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">US Census Bureau, Supplemental Poverty Measures 2009–2022</a></p>
        <p class="explore-desc">The SPM accounts for government programs like the child tax credit, food assistance, and housing subsidies — making it a more accurate measure of economic hardship than the official poverty rate. The dramatic dip in 2021 shows the direct impact of the expanded CTC.</p>
        <div id="explore-poverty-timeline"></div>
      </div>

      <div class="explore-card">
        <h5>The Cost Comparison: What $100B Bought</h5>
        <p class="explore-source">Sources: <a href="https://www.npr.org/2022/01/27/1075299510/the-expanded-child-tax-credit-briefly-slashed-child-poverty-heres-what-else-it-d" target="_blank" rel="noopener">NPR</a>, <a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2022/11/25/us/politics/child-tax-credit.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">NY Times</a></p>
        <p class="explore-desc">Congress approved $1.7 trillion in 2022 discretionary spending. The expanded child tax credit that halved child poverty cost roughly $100 billion per year — about 6% of total discretionary spending. It was not renewed.</p>
        <div id="explore-spending"></div>
      </div>

      <div class="explore-card">
        <h5>What the Credit Meant Per Family</h5>
        <p class="explore-source">Source: <a href="https://www.npr.org/2022/01/27/1075299510/the-expanded-child-tax-credit-briefly-slashed-child-poverty-heres-what-else-it-d" target="_blank" rel="noopener">NPR</a></p>
        <p class="explore-desc">The expanded CTC sent monthly payments directly to families — $300/month per child under 6, $250/month per child 6–17. For the first time, the credit was fully refundable, reaching the poorest families who previously earned too little to qualify.</p>
        <div id="explore-per-child"></div>
      </div>

      <!-- Additional Resources -->
      <div class="additional-resources">
        <h3>Additional Resources</h3>
        <ul class="resource-list">
          <li>"The SPM child poverty rate more than doubled, from 5.2 to 12.4 percent from 2021 to 2022," <a href="https://www.census.gov/library/publications/2023/demo/p60-280.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><em>Poverty in the United States: 2022</em></a>, US Census, 2023</li>
          <li>C. Turner, <a href="https://www.npr.org/2022/01/27/1075299510/the-expanded-child-tax-credit-briefly-slashed-child-poverty-heres-what-else-it-d" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><em>"The Expanded Child Tax Credit Briefly Slashed Child Poverty,"</em></a> NPR, 2022</li>
          <li>J. DeParle, <a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2022/11/25/us/politics/child-tax-credit.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><em>"The Expanded Child Tax Credit Is Gone. The Battle Over It Remains,"</em></a> NY Times, 2022</li>
        </ul>
        <hr class="resource-divider" />
        <ul class="resource-list">
          <li><a href="https://povertycenter.columbia.edu/publication/2022/child-allowance/benefit-cost-analysis" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><em>"The Benefits and Costs of a U.S. Child Allowance,"</em></a> Columbia University Center on Poverty and Social Policy, 2022</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>
</Poem>

<style>
  /* About & Explore sections */
  .poem-about {
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    padding: var(--space-lg) 0;
  }
  .explore {
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    padding: var(--space-lg) 0;
  }
  .explore h2 { margin-bottom: 0.25rem; }

  .low-point-chart-wrap {
    max-width: 900px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .low-point-epigraph {
    font-family: 'Playfair Display', Georgia, serif;
    font-size: clamp(1rem, 1.8vw, 1.2rem);
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: #1A1A1A;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  #low-point-chart {
    width: 100%;
    height: 520px;
  }

  .low-point-coda {
    text-align: right;
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
    padding-right: 1rem;
    opacity: 0;
    transition: opacity 0.8s ease;
  }

  .coda-line {
    display: inline-block;
    font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    color: #1A1A1A;
    border: 1.5px solid #1A1A1A;
    padding: 0.3rem 0.7rem;
    margin-left: 0.25rem;
    background: #FAF9F6;
  }

  .coda-line--tilted {
    transform: rotate(3deg);
    display: inline-block;
  }

  .explore-card {
    margin-top: 2.5rem;
    padding: 2rem;
    background: #F0EFEB;
    border-radius: 4px;
  }

  .explore-card h5 {
    font-family: 'Playfair Display', Georgia, serif;
    font-size: 1.15rem;
    font-weight: 400;
    color: #1A1A1A;
    margin-bottom: 0.35rem;
  }

  .explore-source {
    font-size: 0.8rem !important;
    color: #8B6F4E !important;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem !important;
  }

  .explore-source a {
    color: #8B6F4E;
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  .explore-desc {
    font-size: 0.95rem !important;
    line-height: 1.7 !important;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem !important;
  }

  #explore-poverty-timeline {
    width: 100%;
    height: 400px;
  }

  #explore-spending {
    width: 100%;
    height: 350px;
  }

  #explore-per-child {
    width: 100%;
    height: 300px;
  }

  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    #low-point-chart {
      height: 400px;
    }
    #explore-poverty-timeline,
    #explore-spending,
    #explore-per-child {
      height: 300px;
    }
    .explore-card {
      padding: 1.25rem;
    }
  }

  /* ── Additional Resources ───────────────────────────────────── */
  .additional-resources {
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    margin-top: var(--space-lg);
    padding-top: var(--space-md);
  }
  .additional-resources h3 {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
    font-weight: 500;
  }
  .resource-list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
  }
  .resource-list li {
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
  }
  .resource-list li a {
    color: inherit;
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 2px;
  }
  .resource-list li a:hover {
    color: var(--color-text);
  }
  .resource-divider {
    border: none;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    margin: var(--space-sm) 0;
  }
</style>

<script is:inline src="https://cdn.amcharts.com/lib/5/index.js"></script>
<script is:inline src="https://cdn.amcharts.com/lib/5/xy.js"></script>
<script is:inline src="https://cdn.amcharts.com/lib/5/themes/Animated.js"></script>

<script is:inline>
(function () {
  var root = am5.Root.new("low-point-chart");

  root.setThemes([am5themes_Animated.new(root)]);

  // Colors
  var BLACK = am5.color(0x1A1A1A);
  var RED = am5.color(0xD32F2F);
  var BG = am5.color(0xFAF9F6);

  var chart = root.container.children.push(
    am5xy.XYChart.new(root, {
      panX: false,
      panY: false,
      wheelX: "none",
      wheelY: "none",
      paddingTop: 60,
      paddingRight: 80,
      paddingBottom: 10,
      paddingLeft: 10,
      maskContent: false,
    })
  );

  // Data — SPM child poverty rates (US Census, Supplemental Poverty Measures)
  // bulletRotation: 0 = pointing up; 90 = pointing right; follows the line direction
  var data = [
    { year: 2017, rate: 13.0, annotation: null, bullet: "none", bulletRotation: 0 },
    { year: 2018, rate: 13.7, annotation: "By sending up to $300 / kid / month\nto families who lack,", bullet: "triangle", bulletRotation: 95 },
    { year: 2019, rate: 12.6, annotation: null, bullet: "none", bulletRotation: 0 },
    { year: 2020, rate: 9.7, annotation: "the US Government cut\nchildhood poverty way back.", bullet: "triangle", bulletRotation: 130 },
    { year: 2021, rate: 5.2, annotation: "Then stopped.", bullet: "circle", bulletRotation: 0 },
    { year: 2022, rate: 12.4, annotation: null, bullet: "arrow", bulletRotation: 35 },
  ];

  // X Axis
  var xAxis = chart.xAxes.push(
    am5xy.ValueAxis.new(root, {
      min: 2016,
      max: 2023,
      strictMinMax: true,
      renderer: am5xy.AxisRendererX.new(root, {
        minGridDistance: 60,
        strokeOpacity: 1,
        strokeWidth: 1.5,
        stroke: BLACK,
      }),
      numberFormat: "####",
    })
  );
  xAxis.get("renderer").labels.template.setAll({
    fontFamily: "Inter, Helvetica Neue, sans-serif",
    fontSize: 13,
    fill: BLACK,
  });
  xAxis.get("renderer").grid.template.setAll({ visible: false });

  // Y Axis
  var yAxis = chart.yAxes.push(
    am5xy.ValueAxis.new(root, {
      min: 0,
      max: 20,
      strictMinMax: true,
      numberFormat: "#'%'",
      renderer: am5xy.AxisRendererY.new(root, {
        strokeOpacity: 1,
        strokeWidth: 1.5,
        stroke: BLACK,
      }),
    })
  );
  yAxis.get("renderer").labels.template.setAll({
    fontFamily: "Inter, Helvetica Neue, sans-serif",
    fontSize: 13,
    fill: BLACK,
  });
  yAxis.get("renderer").grid.template.setAll({
    strokeOpacity: 0.12,
    stroke: am5.color(0x999999),
  });

  // Y axis label
  var yLabel = yAxis.children.unshift(
    am5.Label.new(root, {
      text: "US Childhood Poverty Rate",
      fontFamily: "Inter, Helvetica Neue, sans-serif",
      fontSize: 12,
      fontStyle: "italic",
      fill: am5.color(0x5A5A5A),
      rotation: -90,
      y: am5.p50,
      centerX: am5.p50,
    })
  );

  // Series
  var series = chart.series.push(
    am5xy.LineSeries.new(root, {
      xAxis: xAxis,
      yAxis: yAxis,
      valueYField: "rate",
      valueXField: "year",
      stroke: BLACK,
      fill: BLACK,
      tooltip: am5.Tooltip.new(root, {
        labelText: "{valueX.formatNumber('####')}: {valueY}%",
        getFillFromSprite: false,
        autoTextColor: false,
      }),
    })
  );

  series.get("tooltip").get("background").setAll({
    fill: BG,
    stroke: BLACK,
    strokeWidth: 1,
  });
  series.get("tooltip").label.setAll({
    fill: BLACK,
    fontFamily: "Inter, Helvetica Neue, sans-serif",
    fontSize: 13,
  });

  series.strokes.template.setAll({
    strokeWidth: 2.5,
  });

  // Custom bullets
  series.bullets.push(function (root, series, dataItem) {
    var d = dataItem.dataContext;
    var container = am5.Container.new(root, {});

    // Bullet shape — triangles rotate to point along the line direction
    if (d.bullet === "triangle" || d.bullet === "arrow") {
      var tri = container.children.push(
        am5.Triangle.new(root, {
          width: 16,
          height: 14,
          fill: RED,
          stroke: RED,
          centerX: am5.p50,
          centerY: am5.p50,
        })
      );
      tri.set("rotation", d.bulletRotation || 0);
    } else if (d.bullet === "circle") {
      container.children.push(
        am5.Circle.new(root, {
          radius: 7,
          fill: RED,
          stroke: RED,
          centerX: am5.p50,
          centerY: am5.p50,
        })
      );
    }

    // Annotations
    if (d.annotation) {
      var lines = d.annotation.split("\n");
      var yOff = d.year === 2021 ? 30 : -25 * lines.length - 15;
      var xOff = 0;

      lines.forEach(function (line, i) {
        container.children.push(
          am5.Label.new(root, {
            text: line,
            fontFamily: "Inter, Helvetica Neue, sans-serif",
            fontSize: 14,
            fill: BLACK,
            centerX: am5.p50,
            y: yOff + i * 24,
            x: xOff,
            background: am5.RoundedRectangle.new(root, {
              fill: BG,
              stroke: BLACK,
              strokeWidth: 1.5,
              cornerRadiusTL: 0,
              cornerRadiusTR: 0,
              cornerRadiusBL: 0,
              cornerRadiusBR: 0,
            }),
            paddingTop: 4,
            paddingBottom: 4,
            paddingLeft: 10,
            paddingRight: 10,
          })
        );
      });
    }

    return am5.Bullet.new(root, { sprite: container });
  });

  // "Spent 16 times more" boxed annotation — starts hidden, revealed with the 2022 arrow
  var spentLabel = chart.plotContainer.children.push(
    am5.Label.new(root, {
      text: "Spent 16 times more on\nother (Discretionary) Acts.",
      fontFamily: "Inter, Helvetica Neue, sans-serif",
      fontSize: 13,
      fill: BLACK,
      rotation: -55,
      x: am5.percent(90),
      y: am5.percent(15),
      dx: 55,
      dy: 15,
      centerX: am5.p50,
      centerY: am5.p100,
      opacity: 0,
      background: am5.RoundedRectangle.new(root, {
        fill: BG,
        stroke: BLACK,
        strokeWidth: 1.5,
        cornerRadiusTL: 0,
        cornerRadiusTR: 0,
        cornerRadiusBL: 0,
        cornerRadiusBR: 0,
      }),
      paddingTop: 6,
      paddingBottom: 6,
      paddingLeft: 12,
      paddingRight: 12,
    })
  );

  // Animate in: start with data at 0, then reveal
  var animatedData = data.map(function (d) {
    return { year: d.year, rate: 0, annotation: d.annotation, bullet: d.bullet, bulletRotation: d.bulletRotation };
  });
  series.data.setAll(animatedData);

  series.appear(4000);
  chart.appear(4000, 400);

  // After initial appear, animate each point to real value
  // Gap between points: 1200ms (2× the original 600ms)
  setTimeout(function () {
    data.forEach(function (d, i) {
      setTimeout(function () {
        series.data.setIndex(i, d);
      }, i * 1200);
    });
  }, 2400);

  // Reveal "Spent 16 times more" label with the 2022 arrow
  // Last point (index 5) fires at 2400 + 5*1200 = 8400ms
  setTimeout(function () {
    spentLabel.set("opacity", 1);
  }, 2400 + 5 * 1200);

  // Reveal coda after all data points have settled (8400ms + 1600ms buffer)
  setTimeout(function () {
    var coda = document.querySelector('.low-point-coda');
    if (coda) coda.style.opacity = '1';
  }, 10000);
})();

// ============================================================
// EXPLORE CHART 1: Extended Poverty Timeline (2009–2022)
// Source: US Census SPM child poverty rates
// ============================================================
(function () {
  var root = am5.Root.new("explore-poverty-timeline");
  root.setThemes([am5themes_Animated.new(root)]);

  var BLACK = am5.color(0x1A1A1A);
  var RED = am5.color(0xD32F2F);
  var ACCENT = am5.color(0x8B6F4E);

  var chart = root.container.children.push(
    am5xy.XYChart.new(root, {
      panX: false,
      panY: false,
      paddingTop: 30,
      paddingRight: 20,
      paddingBottom: 20,
      paddingLeft: 5,
    })
  );

  var data = [
    { year: "2009", rate: 18.7, ctc: false },
    { year: "2010", rate: 18.0, ctc: false },
    { year: "2011", rate: 18.1, ctc: false },
    { year: "2012", rate: 17.3, ctc: false },
    { year: "2013", rate: 16.4, ctc: false },
    { year: "2014", rate: 16.7, ctc: false },
    { year: "2015", rate: 16.1, ctc: false },
    { year: "2016", rate: 15.2, ctc: false },
    { year: "2017", rate: 13.0, ctc: false },
    { year: "2018", rate: 13.7, ctc: false },
    { year: "2019", rate: 12.6, ctc: false },
    { year: "2020", rate: 9.7,  ctc: false },
    { year: "2021", rate: 5.2,  ctc: true },
    { year: "2022", rate: 12.4, ctc: false },
  ];

  var xAxis = chart.xAxes.push(
    am5xy.CategoryAxis.new(root, {
      categoryField: "year",
      renderer: am5xy.AxisRendererX.new(root, { minGridDistance: 50 }),
    })
  );
  xAxis.data.setAll(data);
  xAxis.get("renderer").labels.template.setAll({
    fontFamily: "Inter, sans-serif", fontSize: 11, fill: BLACK,
    rotation: -45, centerY: am5.p50, centerX: am5.p100,
    paddingRight: 5,
  });
  xAxis.get("renderer").grid.template.setAll({ visible: false });

  var yAxis = chart.yAxes.push(
    am5xy.ValueAxis.new(root, {
      min: 0,
      max: 22,
      numberFormat: "#'%'",
      renderer: am5xy.AxisRendererY.new(root, {}),
    })
  );
  yAxis.get("renderer").labels.template.setAll({
    fontFamily: "Inter, sans-serif", fontSize: 11, fill: BLACK,
  });
  yAxis.get("renderer").grid.template.setAll({ strokeOpacity: 0.1 });

  // Highlight CTC period — fill only, suppress the extra axis label
  var rangeDataItem = xAxis.makeDataItem({ category: "2021", endCategory: "2021" });
  var range = xAxis.createAxisRange(rangeDataItem);
  range.get("axisFill").setAll({
    fill: RED,
    fillOpacity: 0.08,
    visible: true,
  });
  range.get("label").setAll({ visible: false });

  var areaSeries = chart.series.push(
    am5xy.LineSeries.new(root, {
      xAxis: xAxis,
      yAxis: yAxis,
      valueYField: "rate",
      categoryXField: "year",
      fill: ACCENT,
      stroke: BLACK,
      tooltip: am5.Tooltip.new(root, {
        labelText: "{categoryX}: {valueY}%",
        getFillFromSprite: false,
        autoTextColor: false,
      }),
    })
  );

  areaSeries.get("tooltip").get("background").setAll({
    fill: am5.color(0xFFFFFF), stroke: BLACK, strokeWidth: 1,
  });
  areaSeries.get("tooltip").label.setAll({
    fill: BLACK, fontFamily: "Inter, sans-serif", fontSize: 13,
  });

  areaSeries.fills.template.setAll({ visible: true, fillOpacity: 0.08 });
  areaSeries.strokes.template.setAll({ strokeWidth: 2.5 });

  areaSeries.bullets.push(function (root, series, dataItem) {
    var d = dataItem.dataContext;
    var color = d.ctc ? RED : ACCENT;
    var radius = d.ctc ? 7 : 3.5;
    return am5.Bullet.new(root, {
      sprite: am5.Circle.new(root, {
        radius: radius, fill: color,
        stroke: am5.color(0xFFFFFF), strokeWidth: 2,
      }),
    });
  });

  // Label for 2021 low point only — offset below the point to avoid overlap
  areaSeries.bullets.push(function (root, series, dataItem) {
    var d = dataItem.dataContext;
    if (!d.ctc) return;
    return am5.Bullet.new(root, {
      locationY: 0,
      sprite: am5.Label.new(root, {
        text: "5.2% — Expanded CTC",
        fontFamily: "Inter, sans-serif",
        fontSize: 11,
        fontWeight: "500",
        fill: RED,
        centerX: am5.p50,
        centerY: 0,
        dy: 12,
      }),
    });
  });

  areaSeries.data.setAll(data);
  areaSeries.appear(1500);
  chart.appear(1000, 100);
})();

// ============================================================
// EXPLORE CHART 2: Spending Comparison (horizontal bars)
// ============================================================
(function () {
  var root = am5.Root.new("explore-spending");
  root.setThemes([am5themes_Animated.new(root)]);

  var BLACK = am5.color(0x1A1A1A);
  var RED = am5.color(0xD32F2F);
  var GRAY = am5.color(0xD4D0C8);

  var chart = root.container.children.push(
    am5xy.XYChart.new(root, {
      panX: false,
      panY: false,
      paddingTop: 10,
      paddingRight: 30,
      paddingLeft: 5,
      paddingBottom: 10,
    })
  );

  var data = [
    { category: "Expanded Child Tax Credit", value: 100, color: RED, label: "$100B/year" },
    { category: "2022 Discretionary Spending", value: 1700, color: GRAY, label: "$1.7 Trillion" },
  ];

  // Horizontal: categories on Y axis, values on X
  var yAxis = chart.yAxes.push(
    am5xy.CategoryAxis.new(root, {
      categoryField: "category",
      renderer: am5xy.AxisRendererY.new(root, {
        cellStartLocation: 0.2,
        cellEndLocation: 0.8,
        minGridDistance: 30,
      }),
    })
  );
  yAxis.data.setAll(data);
  yAxis.get("renderer").labels.template.setAll({
    fontFamily: "Inter, sans-serif", fontSize: 12, fill: BLACK,
    maxWidth: 180, oversizedBehavior: "wrap",
  });
  yAxis.get("renderer").grid.template.setAll({ visible: false });

  var xAxis = chart.xAxes.push(
    am5xy.ValueAxis.new(root, {
      min: 0,
      numberFormat: "'$'#'B'",
      renderer: am5xy.AxisRendererX.new(root, {}),
    })
  );
  xAxis.get("renderer").labels.template.setAll({
    fontFamily: "Inter, sans-serif", fontSize: 11, fill: BLACK,
  });
  xAxis.get("renderer").grid.template.setAll({ strokeOpacity: 0.08 });

  var series = chart.series.push(
    am5xy.ColumnSeries.new(root, {
      xAxis: xAxis,
      yAxis: yAxis,
      valueXField: "value",
      categoryYField: "category",
      tooltip: am5.Tooltip.new(root, {
        labelText: "{label}",
        getFillFromSprite: false,
        autoTextColor: false,
      }),
    })
  );

  series.get("tooltip").get("background").setAll({
    fill: am5.color(0xFFFFFF), stroke: BLACK, strokeWidth: 1,
  });
  series.get("tooltip").label.setAll({
    fill: BLACK, fontFamily: "Inter, sans-serif", fontSize: 13,
  });

  series.columns.template.setAll({
    cornerRadiusTR: 3, cornerRadiusBR: 3, strokeOpacity: 0, height: am5.percent(60),
  });

  series.columns.template.adapters.add("fill", function (fill, target) {
    return target.dataItem.dataContext.color;
  });

  // Value labels at end of bars
  series.bullets.push(function (root, series, dataItem) {
    var d = dataItem.dataContext;
    return am5.Bullet.new(root, {
      locationX: 1,
      sprite: am5.Label.new(root, {
        text: d.label,
        fontFamily: "Inter, sans-serif",
        fontSize: 12,
        fontWeight: "500",
        fill: BLACK,
        centerY: am5.p50,
        dx: 8,
      }),
    });
  });

  series.data.setAll(data);
  series.appear(1500);
  chart.appear(1000, 100);
})();

